Description Title: Remastered Freestanding Federation House with Harbour Views in a Premier Street
Description:
Boasting lift access to spectacular entertaining areas on all three levels and captivating harbour views from the upper floor, this architect-redesigned Federation residence has been artfully transformed into a sumptuous low maintenance beach house for executives, families or downsizers. Fusing inherent features such as high rosette ceilings and timber flooring with superb appointments and sumptuous coastal styling, it showcases a living and dining space flowing via glass bi-folds to a north deck, bespoke basement entertainers' retreat with a timber bar and gas log fireplace plus a pavilion-style top floor entertainment room with a kitchenette and bi-fold windows framing sparkling harbour views. Placed on private easycare gardens in a prestigious quiet tree-lined street, it is 300m to the harbour foreshore and Delwood Beach and less than 700m to Manly Wharf and the gateway to Manly's cosmopolitan cuisine and social scene. 

- Covered verandah dressed in elaborate timber fretwork, wide entrance hall with sculpted archway
- Remarkably bright and airy, glass bi-fold doors/windows, louvered windows and bespoke tropical fans
- White painted timber-paneled ceilings and walls mix plus exposed sandstone feature walls
- Generous living and dining space with wide glass bi-fold doors lining the north and east walls
- Seamless flow to a covered north deck that steps down to a private tree-lined pebbled courtyard 
- Stylish open plan timber bench and gas kitchen plus butler's pantry with dishwasher and second sink
- Sunny top floor family entertainment room with vaulted ceilings, bi-fold windows and harbour views
- Family room has a kitchenette, wine fridge and dishwasher and can form a retreat with main bedroom
- Three bedrooms with built-ins on entry level, main with built-ins and an ensuite on the top floor 
- Home office with under-stair storeroom, stylish white bathrooms with Moroccan Encaustic tiled flooring
- Basement retreat features two separate rooms, sandstone walls, bespoke timber bars and a wine fridge 
- The retreat includes heated polished concrete flooring, a gas log fireplace and a giant storeroom/cellar
- Original timber flooring, plantation shutters, ducted vacuum, video intercom and security alarm
- Car space, hot/cold outdoor shower, low maintenance landscaped gardens, easy walk to Manly Beach

Description Title: Timeless Character and a Setting that will steal your heart
Description:
Approaching via the long driveway, your senses will be captivated by the surrounding lush green grounds, mature trees, manicured hedges, rolling lawns and the magnesium swimming pool. Wide verandas offer a warm welcome to a home that exudes character, charm, and elegance. Perfectly positioned on 5,725m2 of landscaped grounds, just minutes from town but a peaceful retreat from the hectic pace of city living.

High raked ceilings feature throughout the open plan living and dining area with an impressive wood fireplace. This airy central space adjoins a fantastic new kitchen displaying 2 pack cabinetry with soft close doors and drawers, walk-in pantry, 6-burner free standing stove & dual oven, fully integrated dishwasher, and stone bench tops.

Continuing the entertainment options outside, you are spoilt for choice, a covered rear deck aspected to the north, providing a brilliant vantage point for admiring the treed outlook and beautiful magnesium swimming pool. Whilst the front deck takes in the tree top outlook and the more distant views across to Preston.

On the same level, the sizable main bedroom has a walk-in-robe and luxurious ensuite. The kids will enjoy their own space too, downstairs there is a rumpus room opening onto another covered deck, plus there are three more bedrooms and a family bathroom.

Benefitting from a secure 8m long double garage, the property also includes an extra carport, bore to keep your grass green all year round, and rainwater storage totalling 22,500 litres.

Living on acreage in Middle Ridge is a lifestyle high sought, but rarely found. This comfortable home combines the warmth and charm of timber and brick, with terrific updates. Offering a highly functional floor plan and every modern convenience for contemporary family living, here your family can live large, without the restrictions of a suburban sized block, and enjoy absolute peace and privacy in this prestigious enclave.

This is the first time the property has been offered to the market in 50 years, and the owner leaves a legacy of love, laughter and memories. It is now time for a new family to embrace what this home has to offer.

This solid brick 3 bedroom home offers an enclosed garage which has been used as a rumpus to sleep friends and family. The cosy sunken-lounge has a toasty wood fire which heats the entire home. The contemporary kitchen services the dining area and overlooks the heart of the home - which is the spectacular deck - that has been set up for year round entertainment. There is the benefit of two toilets, and all bedrooms are a good size with built-in robes.

The kids can play safely in the fully fenced back yard. Sardon is a beautiful and quiet tree-lined street, conveniently located in the Centenary Heights School Catchment, and a short drive to South -Town Shopping Centre.

Initially, you will be greeted by the charming porch out the front of the house, followed by a living area with plenty of exposure to sunlight. This home is complimented with VJ wall panelling and polished timber floors. The living area leads you through to the rest of the home. The kitchen/dining area has been thoughtfully designed to maximise the space and allow for as much storage space as possible. Complete with quality appliances and a modern finish, the kitchen fits in perfectly with the rest of the home. Both bedrooms are large in size with easy access to the renovated main bathroom. 

At the rear of the home is a large fully fenced backyard and is a blank slate for you to create the backyard of your dreams.
 
Overall features of this property include:
 True character finishes with VJ walls and polished timber flooring
 Plenty of natural light throughout
 Modern finishes with quality appliances in the kitchen
 2 good sized bedrooms
 Renovated throughout
 Single carport
 Fully fenced back yard
 Minutes to the thriving CBD

Description Title: 'Free Haven'
Description:
A classical timeless homestead on a sprawling leafy parcel of land which you'll be proud to come home to. 

A touch of history for sale as 'Free Haven' was the original homestead in the area built in 1904 she has witnessed many changes in Toowoomba's history. 

The current owners have kept 'Free Haven' in the family since 1917 and as you can imagine this is a big decision to pass her on to new custodians.

You'll enjoy tranquillity in the fabulous treed yard on three titles overlooking the park and covering a total 2,486m2. A unique parcel of land with two street frontage and an easy additional two homesites fronting onto Butt Street (subject to TRC approval).

The home is a wonderful blend of old and new with the specialised use of hardwood timber throughout and meticulously handmade iron features are a creation from a master tradesman. 

A joy to inspect from the moment you arrive at the paved driveway and front yard adorned with flora delights. All the class of a bygone era with formal dining and lounge area, VJ's, 6" hoop pine floors, french doors, 10ft 6" ceilings and a quintessential open fireplace. 

Modern kitchen flowing to an inviting informal living area and opening out onto a generous north facing deck overlooking the shaded backyard secluded from the world. 

The transformation on the second level provides the ultimate parents retreat with open plan master bedroom fastidiously built in decadent hardwood timber and ample space in this room to stay all day if you choose! 

Both levels are blessed with North facing alfresco areas promoting lifestyle all year round. 

The family here at 'Free Haven' are proud to offer this grand old lady to the market and classic home buyers are encouraged to book a private viewing.

Description Title: No Deposit Required or Rent2own
Description:
First Step Homes has a solution for Homeownership, whether it's a Rent2own or simply lending you your deposit Plus costs associated with your purchase, e.g. legal, stamp duty, govt & bank charges.

We have many house/land packages or townhouses available across the Eastern Sea Board of Australia.

All building contracts will be a fixed-priced turned-key package, which means that you just move in as all the work has been completed. e.g. Landscaping with fences and driveway, carpet/blinds/clotheslines & letterbox. 

Your new home/townhouse will have all the bells and whistle like an air conditioning split system to cool or heat in those changing seasons. 

The kitchen will have all the modern cons, like an automatic dishwasher with modern appliances. Amazing! Flooring will consist of tiles or planking in the living areas and carpet for all the bedrooms. 

Getting your car in and out of the garage with your remote control will be a breeze. 

With your new home completed, you can relax and enjoy family and friends knowing that you will have no more inspections, no more moving, and no more questions about what pets you can have. WOW, What a Life! 

To see if you qualify for a new home. 

Step 1. Complete Your Name, Email & Mobile Details 

Step 2. We will forward you our Financial Health Check Form to complete; this will only take 2 mins to complete. 

Step 3. We will then contact you about your capacity to move ahead with us. If a Rent2own doesn't appeal to you, we always have a lending arm to lend you your deposit to move ahead with the bank. 

Why choose Rent to Own? How does this work? Why Rent2own? Our Rent2own Program is for individuals and families who do not qualify for traditional mortgage financing. Tenants enrolled in our program have a clear strategy to becoming homeowners soon while improving and building their credit report. 

Being in a Rent2own let you experience the pride of becoming a homeowner. Also, providing you with the freedom to make improvements to your home; at the end of the day, it is your home.

Purchase Price: Locked in purchase price! The purchase price of the house will be locked in for the duration of the program. Rent: Locked in rent for the period of your lease term, allowing you to take the necessary time to either repair your credit or save up more! What are you waiting for? Give us a call and speak with our team today! First Step Home

What you will need to qualify:-
* Income (incl tax) $120,000
* Clean Credit History 
* Paying all your debts on time
We have helped 100s of families around Australia to achieve homeownership.

What are you waiting for?
